  "doc_id": "32206",
  "text": "One disadvantage of pooling or averaging results from right and left eyes is a \"loss\" of information and hence a loss of eYciency, analogous to that which may occur when only a single eye from each individual is used in the analysis (see above). However, the degree of information \"wasted\" by the pooling or averaging of findings is likely to be less than that which occurs when only one eye is included. [CITATION_1] It will depend on the degree of correlation between the right and left eyes, with the greatest loss occurring when this correlation is low.",
